1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,079
It's here. It's here.

2
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,800
Don't go. Come back.

3
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:58,880
We're really far from shore already.
Are you gonna tell me where we're going?

4
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,999
To hell.

5
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,199
Don't. No!

6
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:06,240
This island is cursed.

7
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:17,000
Mook, listen to me first. I'm sorry.

8
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,880
Can we go back
to the way things used to be?

9
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,240
Oh? Come on.

10
00:03:48,280 --> 00:03:49,600
Why did the lights go out now?

11
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,240
The boat's ready.

12
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,440
I'll send him back right now.

13
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:51,199
Why is the water red like blood?

14
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,799
Did someone die inside the water tank?

15
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,479
Oh, there's no way.

16
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,879
The water system
hasn't been used in a long time,

17
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,039
so maybe the water
has some color or smell to it.

18
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,399
But it can't be blood.

19
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:04,039
I just used the water
in the kitchen earlier.

20
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:05,560
Nothing happened at all.

21
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,519
There was.

22
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:10,200
It was in the bathroom.
Go look for yourself.

23
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,520
I already checked.

24
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,799
I'm certain there's nothing wrong.

25
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:22,200
I cleaned this room myself.

26
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:26,000
Da, are you alright?

27
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,399
Mr. Thon,

28
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,759
the water is as red as blood.

29
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:34,280
There has to be something wrong
with this room. I can't stay here.

30
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:38,759
Da, calm down. Maybe you imagined it?

31
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:41,558
I didn't imagine it. I really saw it.

32
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,679
Go look.

33
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:52,200
Da, are you sure you didn't imagine it?

34
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:55,320
I didn't. Why would I lie?

35
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:00,200
There's nothing wrong.

36
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,400
Everything looks normal.

37
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,760
But it really happened earlier.

38
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:09,840
If you can't find anything...

39
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:15,039
If you can't find anything,
it's even scarier.

40
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,999
Mr. Thon, I definitely can't stay here.

41
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,599
I want to change rooms.

42
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:23,120
But there aren't any empty rooms left.

43
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:26,040
Then...

44
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,720
I'll sleep in Mook's room instead.

45
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,119
Please, Mook.

46
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:40,800
Let me stay with you.
Just one night is fine.

47
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,720
Okay.

48
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,840
Ma'am, I'm sorry on behalf of my friend.

49
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:50,400
No problem. I'm going back to work.

50
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:54,880
Hey,

51
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:58,440
if you're going to see your brother off,
go meet us at the pier.

52
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,760
Oh? Win's leaving already?

53
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:12,920
Dara,

54
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,520
this isn't our house.

55
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:20,200
I think we shouldn't cause trouble here.

56
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,400
What a waste of time.
You shouldn't have told me to come here.

57
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,319
How is this only my fault?

58
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:30,320
Next time, I'm not helping you anymore.

59
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:36,240
Get on the boat already.

60
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,760
I'll have the staff take you back.

61
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,239
And if something like this happens again,

62
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:45,520
I'll make you swim back yourself.

63
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,280
Go.

64
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:34,800
Dad.

65
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:36,720
Sarai.

66
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,240
Are you dead?

67
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,520
Sarai.

68
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,360
You can see me?

69
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:53,360
Then that means
when you disappeared from home...

70
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,080
You...

71
00:13:57,320 --> 00:13:59,760
Yes. I died.

72
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,200
But I never imagined you'd die so young.

73
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,000
Sarai,

74
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,160
my poor daughter.

75
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:17,000
Sarai,

76
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:19,800
leave Skull Island immediately.

77
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,360
This island is very dangerous.

78
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:27,760
But I'm already dead.
No one can hurt me anymore.

79
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:32,599
Whether it's spirits like you
or living humans,

80
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:33,880
it spares no one.

81
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,000
What do you mean?

82
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:41,240
There's no time to explain.
You have to leave now.

83
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:45,680
Then come with me. Let's leave together.

84
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,879
I can't. You must go. Trust me.

85
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:51,879
Leave before...

86
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,559
- No.
- Sarai.

87
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,839
- Dad.
- Go, Sarai.

88
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:56,720
Dad.

89
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,600
- Sarai!
- Dad!

90
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:02,040
Go.

91
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:25,560
Are you sure they don't know anything?

92
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:28,760
Fine.

93
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:33,120
Once they leave the island, do it.

94
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:49,079
Pong, I'm done putting the things away.

95
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:50,559
Let's go.

96
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:51,720
Okay.

97
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:56,840
Hey.

98
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:02,480
Woman. Woman.

99
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,240
Woman.

100
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:06,119
What now?

101
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:08,960
So annoying. When's this crazy bastard
gonna die already?

102
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:10,880
Where's the woman?

103
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:12,880
Where's the woman?

104
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:15,359
Huh?

105
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,879
Thrown into the sea. Thrown into the sea.

106
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:19,319
Hey!

107
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,919
Thrown into the sea.

108
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,919
Under the sea.

109
00:16:22,920 --> 00:16:24,480
She's under the sea.

110
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:26,760
Pong.

111
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:29,719
Wait. Hey.

112
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,160
Why'd you hit him?

113
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,640
I lost my temper for a second.

114
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,160
He's so annoying,
rambling nonsense nonstop.

115
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,759
I'm already exhausted.

116
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,959
Whoa.

117
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,200
Take care of him.

118
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:47,600
That was harsh.

119
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,680
MR. PHUM

120
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,920
Why are you going to bed so early tonight?

121
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:26,599
I was tired, so I came up to sleep.
What's strange about that?

122
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:32,240
I thought maybe you changed your mind

123
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,480
and suddenly wanted
to have a child with me.

124
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,720
I'm sleepy.

125
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,919
Wow, it smells good.

126
00:17:58,920 --> 00:18:01,559
I'll take care of it. Go eat.

127
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:02,520
Go.

128
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,159
There are sweet clams too.

129
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,600
They're my favorite.

130
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,079
Ma'am, do we have extra plates and spoons?

131
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:11,559
It's there. Oh.

132
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:14,759
I think those guys took the rest already.

133
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:17,359
I'll go grab some for you in the kitchen.

134
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,720
It's okay, ma'am. I'll get them myself.

135
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,759
Over there, right?

136
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,720
Yes.

137
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,920
Thank you.

138
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:31,319
Here, ma'am, the shrimps are ready.

139
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,240
Here it is.

140
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,040
Hey.

141
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:48,880
What's wrong?

142
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,159
Aren't you going to eat?

143
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,080
Yes, I am.

144
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:57,360
Then sit down.

145
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,519
Well.

146
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:06,360
Guess I'm so hungry I'm hallucinating.

147
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:08,359
Huh?

148
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:09,280
Let's eat, man.

149
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:41,880
Who's there?

150
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,080
Oh my.

151
00:22:02,680 --> 00:22:05,999
Thunder already.

152
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,800
Looks like it's going to rain tonight.

153
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:14,720
Not now, please.
We're just getting to the good part.

154
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:18,879
With wind this cold,
it's definitely going to rain.

155
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,200
I think you're right, ma'am.

156
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:23,959
But what's taking Kaimook so long?

157
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:25,279
Why isn't she back yet?

158
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:28,319
She went to get the plates.
She should be back soon.

159
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:30,319
Let's eat.

160
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:33,159
Otherwise, we won't have
enough time before it rains.

161
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:36,200
Let's eat.

162
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:26,720
What's that light?

163
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:13,720
Kaimook.

164
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:17,040
Mr. Narathon.

165
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:19,400
Where are you going?

166
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:22,520
Well, I...

167
00:24:27,560 --> 00:24:28,920
You said you came for plates,

168
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,879
but you already walked straight through
the kitchen and ended up back here.

169
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,080
Where are you going?

170
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:38,879
Well, I just kept walking
without realizing it.

171
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:40,839
I didn't think it would lead out here.

172
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:43,000
I was about to head back inside already.

173
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:47,280
You shouldn't wander away
from the group for too long.

174
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:49,040
I was worried.

175
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:54,440
Well, I mean, everyone would be worried.

176
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,400
What are you laughing at?

177
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:00,600
Nothing.

178
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,720
Thank you.

179
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:33,040
Isn't it too much?

180
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:36,200
I'm sure you can finish it.

181
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:39,640
You are right.

182
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,640
Thank you.

183
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,399
Are you really
going to eat all that, Mook?

184
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:03,640
Why did you make Mr. Thon
grill you a whole plate?

185
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,880
I want everyone to eat plenty

186
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:11,360
so you'll all
have energy for work tomorrow.

187
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:18,719
Then, grill some for me too, Mr. Thon.

188
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:21,080
I barely ate anything.

189
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,760
Please.

190
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,440
Sure.

191
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:33,320
What do we have?

192
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:45,080
Kaimook, how is the food? Is it good?

193
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:48,200
It's good, but a little burned.

194
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:55,200
Professor, looks like
it's definitely going to rain tonight.

195
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:59,519
Really?
But I checked the weather forecast.

196
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:01,200
There wasn't supposed to be any rain.

197
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:09,440
Anyway, you and Thon
are okay now, right?

198
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,159
What do you mean?

199
00:27:13,160 --> 00:27:17,039
At first, you two seemed like
you couldn't stand each other.

200
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:20,279
But now it looks like
you're getting along just fine.

201
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:22,120
Am I right?

202
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:24,879
Yes.

203
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:27,759
Well, if your friend
didn't keep provoking me,

204
00:27:27,760 --> 00:27:30,320
I wouldn't have any problem with him.

205
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:36,079
What are those?

206
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,919
What are you talking about?

207
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:39,439
Just talking about general stuff,

208
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,080
like the weather and everything.

209
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:44,999
Let's eat from the same plate.

210
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:49,479
Everyone, I think
it's definitely going to rain.

211
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:51,879
You should hurry and finish eating

212
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:53,839
so you can get back to your rooms.

213
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:55,959
I'll start putting things away.

214
00:27:55,960 --> 00:27:58,040
- Okay, ma'am. Thank you so much.
- Alright.

215
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:01,679
Come help me put things away.

216
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:03,040
- Hurry up.
- It's going to rain.

217
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,840
Shall we go?

218
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,840
- Let's go.
- Alright.

219
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:31,080
<i>The number you have dialed
cannot be connected at the moment.</i>

220
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:42,640
<i>The number you have dialed
cannot be connected at the moment.</i>

221
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:48,399
<i>The number you have dialed
cannot be connected at the moment.</i>

222
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:51,679
Honey, come inside already.

223
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,840
Why are you standing
out here getting bitten by mosquitoes?

224
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:56,719
I can't reach Mook at all.

225
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,119
Oh.

226
00:28:58,120 --> 00:29:01,559
She already told us the phone signal
on Skull Island is terrible.

227
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:03,840
If there's signal, she'll call us herself.

228
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:07,719
But she should have called.

229
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,440
What if something happened?

230
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:14,519
She went there for an internship,
not a vacation.

231
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:17,280
She's probably just very busy.
Nothing's wrong.

232
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,320
Go to bed already.

233
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:32,799
Every time you don't get enough sleep,
you wake up with a headache.

234
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:34,439
If you keep stressing like this,

235
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:36,280
you won't be able to sleep again.

236
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:43,120
Looks like I'll have to light
some herbal scented candles.

237
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:47,519
No need. I'm sleepy already.

238
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:49,239
I can fall asleep on my own.

239
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:51,320
Don't light your candles.

240
00:29:57,080 --> 00:30:00,720
If Mr. Narathon weren't Mr. Phum's son,

241
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,200
you wouldn't be this worried about Mook.

242
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:07,240
I don't understand
why you hate Mr. Phum so much.

243
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:24,639
Boys, are you done cleaning up yet?

244
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:27,439
If you are,
come help me wash the dishes over here.

245
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,559
Yes, ma'am.

246
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,999
If the rain starts pouring,

247
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,719
it'll be hard getting back.

248
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:35,200
- Let me help.
- Clean this.

249
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:40,959
My goodness.

250
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,080
Oh.

251
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:47,879
Dear spirits, if it's going to rain,
a storm's coming, the power's going out,

252
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,439
please wait just a little longer.

253
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:51,999
Let us all get back safely first.

254
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,239
<i>Sathu.</i>

255
00:30:54,240 --> 00:30:55,279
Ma'am.

256
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:57,599
<i>Sathu.</i>

257
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:59,479
My goodness.

258
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,039
- Oh.
- Ma'am.

259
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:03,599
- The power's gone out.
- We're screwed now.

260
00:31:03,600 --> 00:31:05,799
What do you mean screwed?

261
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:08,279
The lamp's over there.

262
00:31:08,280 --> 00:31:10,760
- Go get it.
- Yes, ma'am.

263
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,039
Hurry up.

264
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,280
Okay.

265
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:18,239
Here it is.

266
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,439
Alright.

267
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:22,520
Hey, hurry up.

268
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:24,160
That...

269
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:25,759
What's that?

270
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:27,920
Where? What?

271
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:31,799
- Where is it?
- There.

272
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:33,199
Is that a person?

273
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:35,040
- Where?
- Over there.

274
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:38,120
I don't see anything.

275
00:31:40,560 --> 00:31:42,959
- Hey!
- What?

276
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:44,320
A ghost!

277
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,559
- What?
- A ghost!

278
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:50,360
Over there. It's there.

279
00:31:50,960 --> 00:31:53,359
- There's nothing.
- It's over there.

280
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:55,159
Screw this! I'm outta here!

281
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:57,279
- A ghost!
- Hey.

282
00:31:57,280 --> 00:32:00,039
What's wrong with him? Come back.

283
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:01,759
Ma'am, what's wrong with him?

284
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,439
I don't know.

285
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:06,799
I've got goosebumps.

286
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:10,240
Let's go back. We can clean it tomorrow.

287
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:14,839
Please don't rain yet.

288
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:16,760
Let us make it back safely first.

289
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:23,600
Why did you stop?

290
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:29,759
Did you see something too?

291
00:32:29,760 --> 00:32:31,079
Did you?

292
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:34,679
Right. Who was walking behind us?

293
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:36,720
Everyone already went back to their rooms.

294
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:38,280
Yeah.

295
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:57,839
Oh.

296
00:32:57,840 --> 00:32:59,440
There's no one.

297
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:01,840
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

298
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:06,120
Get out of this island!

299
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:10,559
Ma'am, what are you waiting for?

300
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:11,800
Let's go. Hurry up.

301
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,320
Don't come out, Kaimook.

302
00:35:10,520 --> 00:35:12,080
Who locked the door?

303
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:19,720
Is someone out there?
Please open the door.

304
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:25,600
Is someone out there?
Please open the door.

305
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:40,799
It's really late. Go to sleep already.

306
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,280
I'm just done with this.

307
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,680
Is someone out there?
Please open the door.

308
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:53,120
Sounds like it came from Kaimook's room.

309
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,760
What's going on, Mook?

310
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:07,040
What's wrong with the door?

311
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,920
It won't open.

312
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:25,440
What do we do?

313
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:35,360
Kaimook, is something wrong?

314
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:39,639
You scared me.

315
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:43,479
We heard someone banging on the door.
What happened?

316
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:45,039
I have no idea.

317
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:47,719
I woke up and saw Mook banging on the door

318
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:49,400
saying it wouldn't open.

319
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:53,080
But you opened it just fine.
Nothing's wrong.

320
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:57,920
But it really wouldn't open earlier.

321
00:36:58,480 --> 00:37:00,600
It felt like someone
was pulling it shut from outside.

322
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:04,800
That's why I kept banging on the door
so someone would hear me.

323
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,759
I think if you're not losing your mind,
then you must've been sleepwalking.

324
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:10,839
Look, you woke everybody up.

325
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:12,760
We have to get up early tomorrow too.

326
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:19,080
I'm sorry. I really am sorry.

327
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:21,080
It's okay.

328
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,240
If nothing happened, that's good.

329
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,760
Maybe the door was just stuck.

330
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:29,840
Tomorrow,
I'll have one of the staff check it out.

331
00:37:32,520 --> 00:37:34,600
Excuse us, then.

332
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,960
That's a pretty unexpected way
to get attention.

333
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:09,399
DIVING ROUTE

334
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:13,080
I want the most underwater photos
possible from this area.

335
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:18,280
I'm assigning Ms. Kaimook
to photograph every coral reef.

336
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:24,880
Save Sea allows you to use
the photos you take for your portfolio.

337
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:29,960
I'll handle the video footage myself.

338
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:31,480
That's good.

339
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:35,199
Let me explain a bit more.

340
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,800
We're diving at this location

341
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:40,720
so we can use the underwater images

342
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:45,160
to plan coral reef restoration.

343
00:38:46,840 --> 00:38:49,319
This project sounds so interesting.

344
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:52,359
If there's anything I can help with,
just tell me.

345
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:56,400
I'd be more than happy to.

346
00:38:57,560 --> 00:39:01,960
Thank you. But for now,
you can assist Kaimook first.

347
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:05,360
Once I figure out what suits you best,
I'll let you know.

348
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:12,039
In that video earlier,
you looked so cool, Mr. Thon.

349
00:39:12,040 --> 00:39:13,879
Like a Hollywood movie star.

350
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:17,120
Wait, what movie was it again, Mook?

351
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,999
No idea. I can't remember.

352
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:22,359
No, the one you once told me.

353
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:25,280
I don't think that's really important.

354
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:02,280
Dara.

355
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,040
Hm?

356
00:40:07,120 --> 00:40:08,400
What?

357
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:14,160
You shouldn't have acted
like that during the meeting.

358
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:17,200
Now what, Mook?

359
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:21,119
The way you openly flirted
with Mr. Narathon.

360
00:40:21,120 --> 00:40:24,320
He's our supervisor.
How could you joke around like that?

361
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,919
But that's honestly how I feel.

362
00:40:27,920 --> 00:40:32,040
Mr. Thon is handsome and cool.

363
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:34,400
I was just telling the truth.
Did I do something wrong?

364
00:40:36,280 --> 00:40:40,040
Don't do it again.
I was embarrassed for you.

365
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:44,400
If you don't care about me,
please care about Na.

366
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:56,840
What are you going to do now?

367
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:01,800
Go check out
the shallow-water coral around here.

368
00:41:03,880 --> 00:41:05,119
It's not a vacation.

369
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:08,200
At this rate,
we're going to fail the internship.

370
00:41:09,520 --> 00:41:12,039
This is part of the internship.

371
00:41:12,040 --> 00:41:13,799
Weren't you listening during the meeting?

372
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:17,200
We're part of a coral reef
restoration project.

373
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:19,960
Don't use that as an excuse.

374
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:23,200
Whatever. Do what you want.

375
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,959
- Let me go.
- I won't. I love you.

376
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:11,200
- What are you doing?
- Stop right now.

377
00:43:12,760 --> 00:43:14,000
Mr. Phum.

378
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:18,320
Could Mook's disappearance be because of...

379
00:43:23,600 --> 00:43:24,840
What's going on?

380
00:43:28,880 --> 00:43:30,280
Ghosts are crawling out of the grave!

381
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:09,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
